data.title: Duane Carter
data.meta_description: Duane Carter, Formula 1 driver from 1950 to 1960. Discover season stats and career highlights for each year he's competed in F1.
data.text:
Duane Carter is a American Formula 1 driver born on May 5, 1913. The first race Duane Carter drove was the 1950 Indianapolis 500. Since then Carter has driven 10 races in total.

In these 10 races, Carter won 0 races, finshed on the podium 1 times and scored a total of 6.5 points. The 1960 Indianapolis 500 was the last race Carter has entered.

Duane ended his career driving for Kuzma.
